Triplochiton scleroxylon

    Authority   K. Schum.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Malvales:Sterculiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names ayous
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 10562

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A tall deciduous or evergreen tree reaching a height of 40-50 m and a
   diameter of up to 150 cm. The form is very good with an exceptionally
   straight and cylindrical bole. Mature trees are buttressed.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   African white wood, Obeche, Samba, Wawa, Ayous, Triplochiton.
   FURTHER INF
   Obeche is native of West Africa. It can be found at elevations from sea
   level to 900 m. The latitudinal range of natural occurrence is 0-10Â°N.
   Annual wood production potential is 6-18 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (T. scleroxylon K. Schumann.)
   Webb D 1984 pp 255 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, USE]
   White F 1983 pp 76 79 81
   INSPIRE species 172 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, USE]
   Chaplin G 1993 pp 221-231 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, LIG, USE]

